#: ../../T/the-network.rst:5
msgid "the network"
msgstr "the network"

#: ../../T/the-network.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../T/the-network.rst:10
msgid ""
"Historically, the union of all the major noncommercial, academic, and "
"hacker-oriented networks, such as Internet, the pre-1990 ARPANET, NSFnet, "
"BITNET, and the virtual UUCP and :ref:`Usenet` ‘networks’, plus the "
"corporate in-house networks and commercial timesharing services (such as "
"CompuServe, GEnie and AOL) that gateway to them. A site is generally "
"considered on the network if it can be reached through some combination of "
"Internet-style (\\@-sign) and UUCP (bang-path) addresses. See "
":ref:`Internet`\\, :ref:`bang-path`\\, :ref:`network-address`\\."
msgstr ""
"歴史的には、Internet、1990年以前のARPANET、NSFnet、BITNET、仮想的なUUCPおよび\\ :ref:`Usenet`\\ "
"‘ネットワーク’といった主要な非商用・学術・ハッカー指向のネットワークすべての連合に、それらにゲートウェイする企業の社内ネットワークや商用タイムシェアリングサービス(CompuServe、GEnie、AOLなど)を加えたもの。あるサイトは一般に、Internet方式(\\@記号)とUUCP(バングパス)アドレスの何らかの組み合わせで到達できれば、ネットワーク上にあるとみなされる。\\"
" :ref:`Internet`\\ 、\\ :ref:`bang-path`\\ 、\\ :ref:`network-address`\\ 参照。"

#: ../../T/the-network.rst:15
msgid ""
"Following the mass-culture discovery of the Internet in 1994 and subsequent "
"proliferation of cheap TCP/IP connections, \"the network\" is increasingly "
"synonymous with the Internet itself (as it was before the second wave of "
"wide-area computer networking began around 1980)."
msgstr ""
"1994年のインターネットの大衆文化的発見と、それに続く安価なTCP/IP接続の普及の後、\"the "
"network\"はますますInternetそのものと同義になっている(1980年ごろに広域コンピュータネットワークの第二の波が始まる前にそうだったように)。"

#: ../../T/the-network.rst:18
msgid ""
"A fictional conspiracy of libertarian hacker-subversives and anti-"
"authoritarian monkeywrenchers described in Robert Anton Wilson's novel "
"*Schrödinger's Cat*\\, to which many hackers have subsequently decided they "
"belong (this is an example of :ref:`ha-ha-only-serious`\\)."
msgstr ""
"Robert Anton Wilsonの小説\\ *Schrödinger's Cat*\\ "
"で描かれる、リバタリアンのハッカー破壊工作員と反権威主義のモンキーレンチャーたちの架空の陰謀。多くのハッカーがその後、自分たちはそこに属すると決めた(これは\\"
" :ref:`ha-ha-only-serious`\\ の一例である)。"

#: ../../T/the-network.rst:20
msgid ""
"In sense 1, the network is often abbreviated to the net. \"Are you on the "
"net?\" is a frequent question when hackers first meet face to face, and "
"\"See you on the net!\" is a frequent goodbye."
msgstr ""
"語義1では、the networkはしばしばthe "
"netと略される。「ネットにいるか?」はハッカーが初めて顔を合わせるときによくある質問であり、「ネットで会おう!」はよくある別れの挨拶である。"
